introduction: This video discusses the fundamental concepts of graph theory in data structures. It covers terminologies such as multi-graphs, directed graphs, undirected graphs, degree of vertices, and complete graphs. The video also explains the difference between in-degree and out-degree in directed graphs.

sections.title: Section 1: Introduction to Graphs
content: Explanation of graph as a combination of vertices and edges.
Definition of multi-graph and directed graph.
Discussion on undirected and directed graphs.

sections.title: Section 2: In-Degree and Out-Degree
content: Explanation of in-degree and out-degree in directed graphs.
Examples to illustrate in-degree and out-degree.

sections.title: Section 3: Complete Graphs
content: Definition of complete graph in undirected draft with n vertices and nc2 edges.
Explanation of complete graphs with examples.
Discussion on the importance of complete graphs in graph theory.

sections.title: Section 4: Applications of Graphs
content: Explanation of graph applications in various fields such as social networks, databases, and algorithms.
Discussion on the importance of graph theory in modern computing.
Examples of graph applications with real-world examples.

sections.title: Section 5: Advanced Topics in Graph Theory
content: Explanation of advanced graph theory concepts such as planar graphs, graph coloring, and graph algorithms.
Discussion on the complexity of graph algorithms.
Examples to illustrate advanced graph theory concepts.
